Currently, when an email is sent by Confluence (when a user comments of a page for example), the Summary of the email is the following:
{noformat}
 [prefix] SpaceName > PageName 
{noformat}

The {noformat} [prefix] {noformat} is the only part can be configured. It would be useful to be able to configure the entire Summary, because if we have a long Space Name, only a few characters of the PageName will be displayed:

!really_long.png|thumbnail!

For users that are watching only one space for example, the PageName is more interesting than the SpaceName. 

Also, depending on the mail client used, only a few extra chars in the SpaceName can cause the PageName to not be displayed for complete.

